6. Kuwait

Image Source

Country: Kuwait

Capital: Kuwait City

Workforce: 0.96 million

Occupations: Agriculture, Tourism and Trade, Oil

Tourism accounts for around 5 percent of Kuwait’s GDP. This includes all the tourism and hospitality activities inside the country, as well as all the visitors that come to Kuwait. Around 40 percent of Kuwaitis work in the oil sector, with a pro-manufacturing economy of around 5 percent. It employs another 13 percent of the workforce in the government sector.
